    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-13T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/1734: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-13T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 13, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your telegrams No. 86 of November 5 and No. 88 of November 11. As President
                    Olaya told you that “he is distinctly opposed to legislation causing suspension
                    of present foreign debt service” either directly or through failure to include
                    necessary appropriations in the budget, the Department assumes that he will use
                    his influence to have the appropriation restored when the budget bill is
                    returned to the House. Is final passage of a budget bill probable?</p>
                <p>The Department hopes that Olaya will likewise strongly oppose the bill discussed
                    in paragraph 2 of your No. 88.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
